For example, under the following conditions, the votes contained in one or more electoral packages may be partially counted The results of the protocols do not match; the minutes of the voting count and calculation do not appear officially or it is not in the possession of the chairman of the electoral committee or there are obvious errors or amendments to the protocols.
In addition, the total count of the full-fledged ballots may be made if there is a difference between the alleged winner and the one in second place, which is equal or less than one percent, provided that at the beginning of the session there is an explicit request by the party or coalition president, who is the second of the candidates mentioned.
The vote count may also be taken in its entirety if, after completion of the proper calculation, it is found that the difference between the alleged winner and the candidate is equal or less than one percent in the second place, provided that there is an explicit request by a representative of the party whose candidate has become second. In this case, the electoral packages exposed to a partial count would be excluded.
