The member of the Sisthema Nacional de Investigadores (National Research System Mexico) stated that the vehicle load was another important cause of the occurrence of impact holes. Therefore, the thickness of each layer of the road load must always be relative to the vehicle load and it must be ensured that this regulation is complied with to avoid frequent impact holes.
